Variables:
   Are like boxes/containers that hold value for us, we can charge or reuse the same variable;
There are 8 basic primitive data types:

  Four basic data types to store whole numbers:
   -byte
   -short
   -int
   -long

  Two basic data types to store decimal numbers:
   -float
   -double

  One data type to store single character:
   -char ''

  One data type to store true/false:
   -boolean


Non-Primitive data type:
  -String - most widely used data type in any programming language

